Rank is calculated based on the combination of market cap, trading volume and normalized price. Combining these three criteria, it gives a better sense of top coins, instead of just the market cap. "Rank" column in our coin ranking page. Updates daily.

Normalized price is calculated considering the same number of coin supply as Bitcoin. This gives a good understanding of the price you are actually paying for the coin and if it is overpriced. If the normalized price is unexpectly high for a coin, it is likely to fall sometime soon. Calculation inspired by this article.

Rank difference is the difference in ranks between normalized price rank ("Normalized Rank" in normalized price page and overall rank ("Rank" column in our coin ranking page). Utilize it to find which coins are significantly overpriced (extreme negative values) but not evident. Please note: this is just one factor to find overpriced, undervalued coins. The rank difference by itself should not be used to identify if a coin is good or bad buy. For good buys, consider top coins from our coin ranking page or check our short term good buy suggestions. Only invest after doing fundamental research on these coins.

Volume percentage is the percentage of volume with respect to Bitcoin's trading volume. This gives a good understanding which coins has good volume / liquidity. You should consider higher volume coins for long term or general trading. Low volume coins could be good for quick gains in short term, but might not be good for long term or you could even get stuck even on short term.
Stay away from low volume, overpriced coins, where rank difference is significantly negative or normalized value compared to your known coins doesn't make sense.

Currently, we are only showing at most top 500 coins in each page. We recommend to consider top 50 coins to be safe (except Tether), but top 100 or 200 coins can also be considered if you find a coin exceptional after doing fundamental research.
Market cap and price collected from coinmarketcap.com; max supply collected from coinmarketcap.com and cryptocompare.com/api/, when unavailable, collected from Y2050 supply of onchainfx.com
